bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Albert Bandura is the David Starr Jordan Professor Emeritus of Social Science in Psychology at Stanford University. He is known as the originator of Social Learning Theory and the theoretical construct of Self-Efficacy. He is perhaps most well-known for the 1961 Bobo doll experiment.
